content:
In CRM Analytics, use the Cluster transformation in a Data Prep recipe to segment rows of data into distinct clusters based on common characteristics. For example, you can cluster accounts based on number of employees, numerical rating, and annual revenue.

To create a Cluster transformation:

* In a Transform node of a Data Prep recipe, select any column in the Preview tab.
* Click the Cluster button.
* Enter the number of clusters to create (2-20).
* Select Use optimal number of clusters and let the algorithm determine the best data organization.
* Choose columns used to determine clusters.
* Select an option under Scale Number to rescale the data if needed.

The clustering algorithm determines clusters by comparing values for all selected columns. Preview shows sample cluster values that can change after the recipe runs.

To view the Graph area, click the Collapse button and save the recipe. Run the recipe to assign and view a cluster for each row.

The Cluster transformation uses the K-Means clustering algorithm and detects clusters dynamically during runtime, but they aren't persisted and can change between recipe runs.
title: Cluster Transformation in CRM Analytics
